oves","1 tbsp cumin seeds","1 tbsp black peppercorns","2 dried bay leaves"]},{"title":"Coconut rice","content":["300 g jasmine rice","700 g water","250 g coconut milk","1 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Curry sauce","content":["1 brown onion (approx. 120 g), cut into halves","2 garlic cloves","1 tsp ground turmeric","1 - 2 fresh green chillies, deseeded if preferred and cut into pieces","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","50 g coconut oil","1 tsp salt, plus extra to season","6 ripe Roma tomatoes, cut into halves","400 g coconut milk","3 fresh Kaffir lime leaves, cut into thin slices","2 tsp fish sauce (gluten free)","2 tsp palm sugar","100 g snow peas, cut into thin slices","oil, for greasing","750 g skinless snapper fillets, cut into portions (approx. 8 cm)","freshly ground black pepper, to season","2 sprigs fresh Thai basil, leaves only, for garnishing (optional)"]}],"id":"r117929","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-y3TjSNus9TY\/XZVQgFMFD4I\/AAAAAAAAdB8\/zZHMlLxyjlcKKd5JijlfHig1Ksd0x5BJACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_OvKPItrVwgEqmvQA.png","title":"Coconut fish curry","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"49.8 g","fat":"42 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"75.4 g","calories":"3789 kJ \/ 902 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable storage jar or container, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, 4 serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["You can store leftover Garam masala in a cool, dark place for several months. Use to season Indian or Asian dishes."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 10m","4 portions"]}